  71 def _get_logger(name=None, level="ERROR"):
  72     # type: (Optional[str], str) -> logging.Logger
  73     if not name:
  74         name = __name__
  75     level = getattr(logging, level.upper())
  76     logger = logging.getLogger(name)
  77     logger.setLevel(level)
  78     formatter = logging.Formatter(
  79         "%(levelname)s %(asctime)s %(module)s %(process)d %(thread)d %(message)s"
  80     )
  81     handler = logging.StreamHandler(stream=sys.stderr)
  82     handler.setFormatter(formatter)
  83     logger.addHandler(handler)
  84     return logger

  87 def shell_escape(cmd):
  88     # type: (Union[str, List[str]]) -> str
  89     """Escape strings for use in :func:`~subprocess.Popen` and :func:`run`.
  90 
  91     This is a passthrough method for instantiating a
  92     :class:`~vistir.cmdparse.Script` object which can be used to escape
  93     commands to output as a single string.
  94     """
  95     cmd = Script.parse(cmd)
  96     return cmd.cmdify()

  99 def unnest(elem):
 100     # type: (Iterable) -> Any
 101     """Flatten an arbitrarily nested iterable.
 102 
 103     :param elem: An iterable to flatten
 104     :type elem: :class:`~collections.Iterable`
 105 
 106     >>> nested_iterable = (
 107             1234, (3456, 4398345, (234234)), (
 108                 2396, (
 109                     23895750, 9283798, 29384, (
 110                         289375983275, 293759, 2347, (
 111                             2098, 7987, 27599
 112                         )
 113                     )
 114                 )
 115             )
 116         )
 117     >>> list(vistir.misc.unnest(nested_iterable))
 118     [1234, 3456, 4398345, 234234, 2396, 23895750, 9283798, 29384, 289375983275, 293759,
 119      2347, 2098, 7987, 27599]
 120     """
 121 
 122     if isinstance(elem, Iterable) and not isinstance(elem, six.string_types):
 123         elem, target = tee(elem, 2)
 124     else:
 125         target = elem
 126     if not target or not _is_iterable(target):
 127         yield target
 128     else:
 129         for el in target:
 130             if isinstance(el, Iterable) and not isinstance(el, six.string_types):
 131                 el, el_copy = tee(el, 2)
 132                 for sub in unnest(el_copy):
 133                     yield sub
 134             else:
 135                 yield el
 136 
 137 
 138 def _is_iterable(elem):
 139     # type: (Any) -> bool
 140     if getattr(elem, "__iter__", False) or isinstance(elem, Iterable):
 141         return True
 142     return False
 143

 145 def dedup(iterable):
 146     # type: (Iterable) -> Iterable
 147     """Deduplicate an iterable object like iter(set(iterable)) but order-
 148     preserved."""
 149     return iter(OrderedDict.fromkeys(iterable))

 152 def _spawn_subprocess(
 153     script,  # type: Union[str, List[str]]
 154     env=None,  # type: Optional[Dict[str, str]]
 155     block=True,  # type: bool
 156     cwd=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, Path]]
 157     combine_stderr=True,  # type: bool
 158 ):
 159     # type: (...) -> subprocess.Popen
 160     from distutils.spawn import find_executable
 161 
 162     if not env:
 163         env = os.environ.copy()
 164     command = find_executable(script.command)
 165     options = {
 166         "env": env,
 167         "universal_newlines": True,
 168         "stdout": subprocess.PIPE,
 169         "stderr": subprocess.PIPE if not combine_stderr else subprocess.STDOUT,
 170         "shell": False,
 171     }
 172     if sys.version_info[:2] > (3, 5):
 173         options.update({"universal_newlines": True, "encoding": "utf-8"})
 174     elif os.name != "nt":
 175         options["universal_newlines"] = True
 176     if not block:
 177         options["stdin"] = subprocess.PIPE
 178     if cwd:
 179         options["cwd"] = cwd
 180     # Command not found, maybe this is a shell built-in?
 181     cmd = [command] + script.args
 182     if not command:  # Try to use CreateProcess directly if possible.
 183         cmd = script.cmdify()
 184         options["shell"] = True
 185 
 186     # Try to use CreateProcess directly if possible. Specifically catch
 187     # Windows error 193 "Command is not a valid Win32 application" to handle
 188     # a "command" that is non-executable. See pypa/pipenv#2727.
 189     try:
 190         return subprocess.Popen(cmd, **options)
 191     except WindowsError as e:  # pragma: no cover
 192         if getattr(e, "winerror", 9999) != 193:
 193             raise
 194     options["shell"] = True
 195     # Try shell mode to use Windows's file association for file launch.
 196     return subprocess.Popen(script.cmdify(), **options)

 199 class SubprocessStreamWrapper(object):
 200     def __init__(
 201         self,
 202         display_stderr_maxlen=200,  # type: int
 203         display_line_for_loops=20,  # type: int
 204         subprocess=None,  # type: subprocess.Popen
 205         spinner=None,  # type: Optional[VistirSpinner]
 206         verbose=False,  # type: bool
 207         stdout_allowed=False,  # type: bool
 208     ):
 209         # type: (...) -> None
 210         stdout_encoding = None
 211         stderr_encoding = None
 212         preferred_encoding = getpreferredencoding()
 213         if subprocess is not None:
 214             stdout_encoding = self.get_subprocess_encoding(subprocess, "stdout")
 215             stderr_encoding = self.get_subprocess_encoding(subprocess, "stderr")
 216         self.stdout_encoding = stdout_encoding or preferred_encoding
 217         self.stderr_encoding = stderr_encoding or preferred_encoding
 218         self.stdout_lines = []
 219         self.text_stdout_lines = []
 220         self.stderr_lines = []
 221         self.text_stderr_lines = []
 222         self.display_line = ""
 223         self.display_line_loops_displayed = 0
 224         self.display_line_shown_for_loops = display_line_for_loops
 225         self.display_line_max_len = display_stderr_maxlen
 226         self.spinner = spinner
 227         self.stdout_allowed = stdout_allowed
 228         self.verbose = verbose
 229         self._iterated_stdout = None
 230         self._iterated_stderr = None
 231         self._subprocess = subprocess
 232         self._queues = {
 233             "streams": Queue(),
 234             "lines": Queue(),
 235         }
 236         self._threads = {
 237             stream_name: threading.Thread(
 238                 target=self.enqueue_stream,
 239                 args=(self._subprocess, stream_name, self._queues["streams"]),
 240             )
 241             for stream_name in ("stdout", "stderr")
 242         }
 243         self._threads["watcher"] = threading.Thread(
 244             target=self.process_output_lines,
 245             args=(self._queues["streams"], self._queues["lines"]),
 246         )
 247         self.start_threads()
 248 
 249     def enqueue_stream(self, proc, stream_name, queue):
 250         # type: (subprocess.Popen, str, Queue) -> None
 251         if not getattr(proc, stream_name, None):
 252             queue.put(("stderr", None))
 253         else:
 254             for line in iter(getattr(proc, stream_name).readline, ""):
 255                 queue.put((stream_name, line))
 256             getattr(proc, stream_name).close()
 257 
 258     @property
 259     def stderr(self):
 260         return self._subprocess.stderr
 261 
 262     @property
 263     def stdout(self):
 264         return self._subprocess.stdout

 266     @classmethod
 267     def get_subprocess_encoding(cls, cmd_instance, stream_name):
 268         # type: (subprocess.Popen, str) -> Optional[str]
 269         stream = getattr(cmd_instance, stream_name, None)
 270         if stream is not None:
 271             return get_output_encoding(getattr(stream, "encoding", None))
 272         return None
 273 
 274     @property
 275     def stdout_iter(self):
 276         if self._iterated_stdout is None and self.stdout:
 277             self._iterated_stdout = iter(self.stdout.readline, "")
 278         return self._iterated_stdout
 279 
 280     @property
 281     def stderr_iter(self):
 282         if self._iterated_stderr is None and self.stderr:
 283             self._iterated_stderr = iter(self.stderr.readline, "")
 284         return self._iterated_stderr
 285 
 286     def _decode_line(self, line, encoding):
 287         # type: (Union[str, bytes], str) -> str
 288         if isinstance(line, six.binary_type):
 289             line = to_text(
 290                 line.decode(encoding, errors=_fs_decode_errors).encode(
 291                     "utf-8", errors=_fs_encode_errors
 292                 ),
 293                 errors="backslashreplace",
 294             )
 295         else:
 296             line = to_text(line, encoding=encoding, errors=_fs_encode_errors)
 297         return line
 298 
 299     def start_threads(self):
 300         for thread in self._threads.values():
 301             thread.daemon = True
 302             thread.start()
 303 
 304     @property
 305     def subprocess(self):
 306         return self._subprocess

 308     @property
 309     def out(self):
 310         # type: () -> str
 311         return getattr(self.subprocess, "out", "")
 312

 315         # type: (str) -> None
 316         self._subprocess.out = value

 325         # type: (str) -> None

 328     def poll(self):
 329         # type: () -> Optional[int]
 330         return self.subprocess.poll()
 331 
 332     def wait(self, timeout=None):
 333         # type: (self, Optional[int]) -> Optional[int]
 334         kwargs = {}
 335         if sys.version_info[0] >= 3:
 336             kwargs = {"timeout": timeout}
 337         result = self._subprocess.wait(**kwargs)
 338         self.gather_output()
 339         return result
 340 
 341     @property
 342     def returncode(self):
 343         # type: () -> Optional[int]
 344         return self.subprocess.returncode
 345 
 346     @property
 347     def text_stdout(self):
 348         return os.linesep.join(self.text_stdout_lines)
 349 
 350     @property
 351     def text_stderr(self):
 352         return os.linesep.join(self.text_stderr_lines)
 353 
 354     @property
 355     def stderr_closed(self):
 356         # type: () -> bool
 357         return self.stderr is None or (self.stderr is not None and self.stderr.closed)
 358 
 359     @property
 360     def stdout_closed(self):
 361         # type: () -> bool
 362         return self.stdout is None or (self.stdout is not None and self.stdout.closed)
 363 
 364     @property
 365     def running(self):
 366         # type: () -> bool
 367         return any(t.is_alive() for t in self._threads.values()) or not all(
 368             [self.stderr_closed, self.stdout_closed, self.subprocess_finished]
 369         )
 370 
 371     @property
 372     def subprocess_finished(self):
 373         if self._subprocess is None:
 374             return False
 375         return (
 376             self._subprocess.poll() is not None or self._subprocess.returncode is not None
 377         )
 378 
 379     def update_display_line(self, new_line):
 380         # type: () -> None
 381         if self.display_line:
 382             if new_line != self.display_line:
 383                 self.display_line_loops_displayed = 0
 384                 new_line = fs_str("{}".format(new_line))
 385                 if len(new_line) > self.display_line_max_len:
 386                     new_line = "{}...".format(new_line[: self.display_line_max_len])
 387                 self.display_line = new_line
 388             elif self.display_line_loops_displayed >= self.display_line_shown_for_loops:
 389                 self.display_line = ""
 390                 self.display_line_loops_displayed = 0
 391             else:
 392                 self.display_line_loops_displayed += 1
 393         return None
 394 
 395     @classmethod
 396     def check_line_content(cls, line):
 397         # type: (Optional[str]) -> bool
 398         return line is not None and line != ""
 399 
 400     def get_line(self, queue):
 401         # type: (Queue) -> Tuple[Optional[str], ...]
 402         stream, result = None, None
 403         try:
 404             stream, result = queue.get_nowait()
 405         except Empty:
 406             result = None
 407         return stream, result
 408 
 409     def process_output_lines(self, recv_queue, line_queue):
 410         # type: (Queue, Queue) -> None
 411         stream, line = self.get_line(recv_queue)
 412         while self.poll() is None or line is not None:
 413             if self.check_line_content(line):
 414                 line = to_text("{}".format(line).rstrip())
 415                 line_queue.put((stream, line))
 416             stream, line = self.get_line(recv_queue)
 417 
 418     def gather_output(self, spinner=None, stdout_allowed=False, verbose=False):
 419         # type: (Optional[VistirSpinner], bool, bool) -> None
 420         if not getattr(self._subprocess, "out", None):
 421             self._subprocess.out = ""
 422         if not getattr(self._subprocess, "err", None):
 423             self._subprocess.err = ""
 424         if not self._queues["streams"].empty():
 425             self.process_output_lines(self._queues["streams"], self._queues["lines"])
 426         while not self._queues["lines"].empty():
 427             try:
 428                 stream_name, line = self._queues["lines"].get()
 429             except Empty:
 430                 if not self._threads["watcher"].is_active():
 431                     break
 432                 pass
 433             if stream_name == "stdout":
 434                 text_line = self._decode_line(line, self.stdout_encoding)
 435                 self.text_stdout_lines.append(text_line)
 436                 self.out += "{}\n".format(text_line)
 437                 if verbose:
 438                     _write_subprocess_result(
 439                         line, "stdout", spinner=spinner, stdout_allowed=stdout_allowed
 440                     )
 441             else:
 442                 text_err = self._decode_line(line, self.stderr_encoding)
 443                 self.text_stderr_lines.append(text_err)
 444                 self.update_display_line(line)
 445                 self.err += "{}\n".format(text_err)
 446                 _write_subprocess_result(
 447                     line, "stderr", spinner=spinner, stdout_allowed=stdout_allowed
 448                 )
 449             if spinner:
 450                 spinner.text = to_native_string(
 451                     "{} {}".format(spinner.text, self.display_line)
 452                 )
 453         self.out = self.out.strip()
 454         self.err = self.err.strip()
 455 
 456 
 457 def _write_subprocess_result(result, stream_name, spinner=None, stdout_allowed=False):
 458     # type: (str, str, Optional[VistirSpinner], bool) -> None
 459     if not stdout_allowed and stream_name == "stdout":
 460         stream_name = "stderr"
 461     if spinner:
 462         spinner.hide_and_write(result, target=getattr(spinner, stream_name))
 463     else:
 464         target_stream = getattr(sys, stream_name)
 465         target_stream.write(result)
 466         target_stream.flush()
 467     return None

 470 def attach_stream_reader(
 471     cmd_instance, verbose, maxlen, spinner=None, stdout_allowed=False
 472 ):
 473     streams = SubprocessStreamWrapper(
 474         subprocess=cmd_instance,
 475         display_stderr_maxlen=maxlen,
 476         spinner=spinner,
 477         verbose=verbose,
 478         stdout_allowed=stdout_allowed,
 479     )
 480     streams.gather_output(spinner=spinner, verbose=verbose, stdout_allowed=stdout_allowed)
 481     return streams

 484 def _handle_nonblocking_subprocess(c, spinner=None):
 485     while c.running:
 486         c.wait()
 487     if spinner:
 488         if c.returncode != 0:
 489             spinner.fail(to_native_string("Failed...cleaning up..."))
 490         elif c.returncode == 0 and not os.name == "nt":
 491             spinner.ok(to_native_string("✔ Complete"))
 492         else:
 493             spinner.ok(to_native_string("Complete"))
 494     return c

 497 def _create_subprocess(
 498     cmd,
 499     env=None,
 500     block=True,
 501     return_object=False,
 502     cwd=os.curdir,
 503     verbose=False,
 504     spinner=None,
 505     combine_stderr=False,
 506     display_limit=200,
 507     start_text="",
 508     write_to_stdout=True,
 509 ):
 510     if not env:
 511         env = os.environ.copy()
 512     try:
 513         c = _spawn_subprocess(
 514             cmd, env=env, block=block, cwd=cwd, combine_stderr=combine_stderr
 515         )
 516     except Exception as exc:  # pragma: no cover
 517         import traceback
 518 
 519         formatted_tb = "".join(traceback.format_exception(*sys.exc_info()))
 520         sys.stderr.write(
 521             "Error while executing command %s:" % to_native_string(" ".join(cmd._parts))
 522         )
 523         sys.stderr.write(formatted_tb)
 524         raise exc
 525     if not block:
 526         c.stdin.close()
 527         spinner_orig_text = ""
 528         if spinner and getattr(spinner, "text", None) is not None:
 529             spinner_orig_text = spinner.text
 530         if not spinner_orig_text and start_text is not None:
 531             spinner_orig_text = start_text
 532         c = attach_stream_reader(
 533             c,
 534             verbose=verbose,
 535             maxlen=display_limit,
 536             spinner=spinner,
 537             stdout_allowed=write_to_stdout,
 538         )
 539         _handle_nonblocking_subprocess(c, spinner)
 540     else:
 541         try:
 542             c.out, c.err = c.communicate()
 543         except (SystemExit, KeyboardInterrupt, TimeoutError):  # pragma: no cover
 544             c.terminate()
 545             c.out, c.err = c.communicate()
 546             raise
 547     if not return_object:
 548         return c.out.strip(), c.err.strip()
 549     return c

 552 def run(
 553     cmd,
 554     env=None,
 555     return_object=False,
 556     block=True,
 557     cwd=None,
 558     verbose=False,
 559     nospin=False,
 560     spinner_name=None,
 561     combine_stderr=True,
 562     display_limit=200,
 563     write_to_stdout=True,
 564 ):
 565     """Use `subprocess.Popen` to get the output of a command and decode it.
 566 
 567     :param list cmd: A list representing the command you want to run.
 568     :param dict env: Additional environment settings to pass through to the subprocess.
 569     :param bool return_object: When True, returns the whole subprocess instance
 570     :param bool block: When False, returns a potentially still-running
 571         :class:`subprocess.Popen` instance
 572     :param str cwd: Current working directory contect to use for spawning the subprocess.
 573     :param bool verbose: Whether to print stdout in real time when non-blocking.
 574     :param bool nospin: Whether to disable the cli spinner.
 575     :param str spinner_name: The name of the spinner to use if enabled, defaults to
 576         bouncingBar
 577     :param bool combine_stderr: Optionally merge stdout and stderr in the subprocess,
 578         false if nonblocking.
 579     :param int dispay_limit: The max width of output lines to display when using a
 580         spinner.
 581     :param bool write_to_stdout: Whether to write to stdout when using a spinner,
 582         defaults to True.
 583     :returns: A 2-tuple of (output, error) or a :class:`subprocess.Popen` object.
 584 
 585     .. Warning:: Merging standard out and standarad error in a nonblocking subprocess
 586         can cause errors in some cases and may not be ideal. Consider disabling
 587         this functionality.
 588     """
 589 
 590     _env = os.environ.copy()
 591     _env["PYTHONIOENCODING"] = str("utf-8")
 592     _env["PYTHONUTF8"] = str("1")
 593     if env:
 594         _env.update(env)
 595     if six.PY2:
 596         _fs_encode = partial(to_bytes, encoding=locale_encoding)
 597         _env = {_fs_encode(k): _fs_encode(v) for k, v in _env.items()}
 598     else:
 599         _env = {k: fs_str(v) for k, v in _env.items()}
 600     if not spinner_name:
 601         spinner_name = "bouncingBar"
 602     if six.PY2:
 603         if isinstance(cmd, six.string_types):
 604             cmd = cmd.encode("utf-8")
 605         elif isinstance(cmd, (list, tuple)):
 606             cmd = [c.encode("utf-8") for c in cmd]
 607     if not isinstance(cmd, Script):
 608         cmd = Script.parse(cmd)
 609     if block or not return_object:
 610         combine_stderr = False
 611     start_text = ""
 612     with spinner(
 613         spinner_name=spinner_name,
 614         start_text=start_text,
 615         nospin=nospin,
 616         write_to_stdout=write_to_stdout,
 617     ) as sp:
 618         return _create_subprocess(
 619             cmd,
 620             env=_env,
 621             return_object=return_object,
 622             block=block,
 623             cwd=cwd,
 624             verbose=verbose,
 625             spinner=sp,
 626             combine_stderr=combine_stderr,
 627             start_text=start_text,
 628             write_to_stdout=write_to_stdout,
 629         )

 632 def load_path(python):
 633     """Load the :mod:`sys.path` from the given python executable's environment
 634     as json.
 635 
 636     :param str python: Path to a valid python executable
 637     :return: A python representation of the `sys.path` value of the given python
 638         executable.
 639     :rtype: list
 640 
 641     >>> load_path("/home/user/.virtualenvs/requirementslib-5MhGuG3C/bin/python")
 642     ['', '/home/user/.virtualenvs/requirementslib-5MhGuG3C/lib/python37.zip',
 643      '/home/user/.virtualenvs/requirementslib-5MhGuG3C/lib/python3.7',
 644      '/home/user/.virtualenvs/requirementslib-5MhGuG3C/lib/python3.7/lib-dynload',
 645      '/home/user/.pyenv/versions/3.7.0/lib/python3.7',
 646      '/home/user/.virtualenvs/requirementslib-5MhGuG3C/lib/python3.7/site-packages',
 647      '/home/user/git/requirementslib/src']
 648     """
 649 
 650     python = Path(python).as_posix()
 651     out, err = run(
 652         [python, "-c", "import json, sys; print(json.dumps(sys.path))"], nospin=True
 653     )
 654     if out:
 655         return json.loads(out)
 656     else:
 657         return []

 660 def partialclass(cls, *args, **kwargs):
 661     """Returns a partially instantiated class.
 662 
 663     :return: A partial class instance
 664     :rtype: cls
 665 
 666     >>> source = partialclass(Source, url="https://pypi.org/simple")
 667     >>> source
 668     <class '__main__.Source'>
 669     >>> source(name="pypi")
 670     >>> source.__dict__
 671     mappingproxy({
 672         '__module__': '__main__',
 673         '__dict__': <attribute '__dict__' of 'Source' objects>,
 674         '__weakref__': <attribute '__weakref__' of 'Source' objects>,
 675         '__doc__': None,
 676         '__init__': functools.partialmethod(
 677             <function Source.__init__ at 0x7f23af429bf8>, , url='https://pypi.org/simple'
 678         )
 679     })
 680     >>> new_source = source(name="pypi")
 681     >>> new_source
 682     <__main__.Source object at 0x7f23af189b38>
 683     >>> new_source.__dict__
 684     {'url': 'https://pypi.org/simple', 'verify_ssl': True, 'name': 'pypi'}
 685     """
 686 
 687     name_attrs = [
 688         n
 689         for n in (getattr(cls, name, str(cls)) for name in ("__name__", "__qualname__"))
 690         if n is not None
 691     ]
 692     name_attrs = name_attrs[0]
 693     type_ = type(
 694         name_attrs, (cls,), {"__init__": partialmethod(cls.__init__, *args, **kwargs)}
 695     )
 696     # Swiped from attrs.make_class
 697     try:
 698         type_.__module__ = sys._getframe(1).f_globals.get("__name__", "__main__")
 699     except (AttributeError, ValueError):  # pragma: no cover
 700         pass  # pragma: no cover
 701     return type_

 704 # Borrowed from django -- force bytes and decode -- see link for details:
 705 # https://github.com/django/django/blob/fc6b90b/django/utils/encoding.py#L112
 706 def to_bytes(string, encoding="utf-8", errors=None):
 707     """Force a value to bytes.
 708 
 709     :param string: Some input that can be converted to a bytes.
 710     :type string: str or bytes unicode or a memoryview subclass
 711     :param encoding: The encoding to use for conversions, defaults to "utf-8"
 712     :param encoding: str, optional
 713     :return: Corresponding byte representation (for use in filesystem operations)
 714     :rtype: bytes
 715     """
 716 
 717     unicode_name = get_canonical_encoding_name("utf-8")
 718     if not errors:
 719         if get_canonical_encoding_name(encoding) == unicode_name:
 720             if six.PY3 and os.name == "nt":
 721                 errors = "surrogatepass"
 722             else:
 723                 errors = "surrogateescape" if six.PY3 else "ignore"
 724         else:
 725             errors = "strict"
 726     if isinstance(string, bytes):
 727         if get_canonical_encoding_name(encoding) == unicode_name:
 728             return string
 729         else:
 730             return string.decode(unicode_name).encode(encoding, errors)
 731     elif isinstance(string, memoryview):
 732         return string.tobytes()
 733     elif not isinstance(string, six.string_types):  # pragma: no cover
 734         try:
 735             if six.PY3:
 736                 return six.text_type(string).encode(encoding, errors)
 737             else:
 738                 return bytes(string)
 739         except UnicodeEncodeError:
 740             if isinstance(string, Exception):
 741                 return b" ".join(to_bytes(arg, encoding, errors) for arg in string)
 742             return six.text_type(string).encode(encoding, errors)
 743     else:
 744         return string.encode(encoding, errors)
 745 
 746 
 747 def to_text(string, encoding="utf-8", errors=None):
 748     """Force a value to a text-type.
 749 
 750     :param string: Some input that can be converted to a unicode representation.
 751     :type string: str or bytes unicode
 752     :param encoding: The encoding to use for conversions, defaults to "utf-8"
 753     :param encoding: str, optional
 754     :return: The unicode representation of the string
 755     :rtype: str
 756     """
 757 
 758     unicode_name = get_canonical_encoding_name("utf-8")
 759     if not errors:
 760         if get_canonical_encoding_name(encoding) == unicode_name:
 761             if six.PY3 and os.name == "nt":
 762                 errors = "surrogatepass"
 763             else:
 764                 errors = "surrogateescape" if six.PY3 else "ignore"
 765         else:
 766             errors = "strict"
 767     if issubclass(type(string), six.text_type):
 768         return string
 769     try:
 770         if not issubclass(type(string), six.string_types):
 771             if six.PY3:
 772                 if isinstance(string, bytes):
 773                     string = six.text_type(string, encoding, errors)
 774                 else:
 775                     string = six.text_type(string)
 776             elif hasattr(string, "__unicode__"):  # pragma: no cover
 777                 string = six.text_type(string)
 778             else:
 779                 string = six.text_type(bytes(string), encoding, errors)
 780         else:
 781             string = string.decode(encoding, errors)
 782     except UnicodeDecodeError:  # pragma: no cover
 783         string = " ".join(to_text(arg, encoding, errors) for arg in string)
 784     return string

 787 def divide(n, iterable):
 788     """split an iterable into n groups, per https://more-
 789     itertools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api.html#grouping.
 790 
 791     :param int n: Number of unique groups
 792     :param iter iterable: An iterable to split up
 793     :return: a list of new iterables derived from the original iterable
 794     :rtype: list
 795     """
 796 
 797     seq = tuple(iterable)
 798     q, r = divmod(len(seq), n)
 799 
 800     ret = []
 801     for i in range(n):
 802         start = (i * q) + (i if i < r else r)
 803         stop = ((i + 1) * q) + (i + 1 if i + 1 < r else r)
 804         ret.append(iter(seq[start:stop]))
 805 
 806     return ret

 809 def take(n, iterable):
 810     """Take n elements from the supplied iterable without consuming it.
 811 
 812     :param int n: Number of unique groups
 813     :param iter iterable: An iterable to split up
 814 
 815     from https://github.com/erikrose/more-itertools/blob/master/more_itertools/recipes.py
 816     """
 817 
 818     return list(islice(iterable, n))

 820 
 821 def chunked(n, iterable):
 822     """Split an iterable into lists of length *n*.
 823 
 824     :param int n: Number of unique groups
 825     :param iter iterable: An iterable to split up
 826 
 827     from https://github.com/erikrose/more-itertools/blob/master/more_itertools/more.py
 828     """
 829 
 830     return iter(partial(take, n, iter(iterable)), [])

 839 def getpreferredencoding():
 840     """Determine the proper output encoding for terminal rendering."""
 841 
 842     # Borrowed from Invoke
 843     # (see https://github.com/pyinvoke/invoke/blob/93af29d/invoke/runners.py#L881)
 844     _encoding = sys.getdefaultencoding() or locale.getpreferredencoding(False)
 845     if six.PY2 and not sys.platform == "win32":
 846         _default_encoding = locale.getdefaultlocale()[1]

 848             _encoding = _default_encoding

 854 
 855 def get_output_encoding(source_encoding):
 856     """Given a source encoding, determine the preferred output encoding.
 857 
 858     :param str source_encoding: The encoding of the source material.
 859     :returns: The output encoding to decode to.
 860     :rtype: str
 861     """
 862 
 863     if source_encoding is not None:
 864         if get_canonical_encoding_name(source_encoding) == "ascii":
 865             return "utf-8"
 866         return get_canonical_encoding_name(source_encoding)
 867     return get_canonical_encoding_name(PREFERRED_ENCODING)

 870 def _encode(output, encoding=None, errors=None, translation_map=None):
 871     if encoding is None:
 872         encoding = PREFERRED_ENCODING
 873     try:
 874         output = output.encode(encoding)
 875     except (UnicodeDecodeError, UnicodeEncodeError):
 876         if translation_map is not None:
 877             if six.PY2:
 878                 output = unicode.translate(  # noqa: F821
 879                     to_text(output, encoding=encoding, errors=errors), translation_map
 880                 )
 881             else:
 882                 output = output.translate(translation_map)
 883         else:
 884             output = to_text(output, encoding=encoding, errors=errors)
 885     except AttributeError:
 886         pass
 887     return output

 890 def decode_for_output(output, target_stream=None, translation_map=None):
 891     """Given a string, decode it for output to a terminal.
 892 
 893     :param str output: A string to print to a terminal
 894     :param target_stream: A stream to write to, we will encode to target this stream if
 895         possible.
 896     :param dict translation_map: A mapping of unicode character ordinals to replacement
 897         strings.
 898     :return: A re-encoded string using the preferred encoding
 899     :rtype: str
 900     """
 901 
 902     if not isinstance(output, six.string_types):
 903         return output
 904     encoding = None
 905     if target_stream is not None:
 906         encoding = getattr(target_stream, "encoding", None)
 907     encoding = get_output_encoding(encoding)
 908     try:
 909         output = _encode(output, encoding=encoding, translation_map=translation_map)
 910     except (UnicodeDecodeError, UnicodeEncodeError):
 911         output = to_native_string(output)
 912         output = _encode(
 913             output, encoding=encoding, errors="replace", translation_map=translation_map
 914         )
 915     return to_text(output, encoding=encoding, errors="replace")

 918 def get_canonical_encoding_name(name):
 919     # type: (str) -> str
 920     """Given an encoding name, get the canonical name from a codec lookup.
 921 
 922     :param str name: The name of the codec to lookup
 923     :return: The canonical version of the codec name
 924     :rtype: str
 925     """
 926 
 927     import codecs
 928 
 929     try:
 930         codec = codecs.lookup(name)
 931     except LookupError:
 932         return name
 933     else:
 934         return codec.name

 937 def _is_binary_buffer(stream):
 938     try:
 939         stream.write(b"")
 940     except Exception:
 941         try:
 942             stream.write("")
 943         except Exception:
 944             pass
 945         return False
 946     return True
 947 
 948 
 949 def _get_binary_buffer(stream):
 950     if six.PY3 and not _is_binary_buffer(stream):
 951         stream = getattr(stream, "buffer", None)
 952         if stream is not None and _is_binary_buffer(stream):
 953             return stream
 954     return stream

 957 def get_wrapped_stream(stream, encoding=None, errors="replace"):
 958     """Given a stream, wrap it in a `StreamWrapper` instance and return the
 959     wrapped stream.
 960 
 961     :param stream: A stream instance to wrap
 962     :param str encoding: The encoding to use for the stream
 963     :param str errors: The error handler to use, default "replace"
 964     :returns: A new, wrapped stream
 965     :rtype: :class:`StreamWrapper`
 966     """
 967 
 968     if stream is None:
 969         raise TypeError("must provide a stream to wrap")
 970     stream = _get_binary_buffer(stream)
 971     if stream is not None and encoding is None:
 972         encoding = "utf-8"
 973     if not encoding:
 974         encoding = get_output_encoding(getattr(stream, "encoding", None))
 975     else:
 976         encoding = get_canonical_encoding_name(encoding)
 977     return StreamWrapper(stream, encoding, errors, line_buffering=True)

 979 
 980 class StreamWrapper(io.TextIOWrapper):
 981 
 982     """This wrapper class will wrap a provided stream and supply an interface
 983     for compatibility."""
 984 
 985     def __init__(self, stream, encoding, errors, line_buffering=True, **kwargs):
 986         self._stream = stream = _StreamProvider(stream)
 987         io.TextIOWrapper.__init__(
 988             self, stream, encoding, errors, line_buffering=line_buffering, **kwargs
 989         )
 990 
 991     # borrowed from click's implementation of stream wrappers, see
 992     # https://github.com/pallets/click/blob/6cafd32/click/_compat.py#L64
 993     if six.PY2:
 994 
 995         def write(self, x):
 996             if isinstance(x, (str, buffer, bytearray)):  # noqa: F821
 997                 try:
 998                     self.flush()
 999                 except Exception:
1000                     pass
1001                 # This is modified from the initial implementation to rely on
1002                 # our own decoding functionality to preserve unicode strings where
1003                 # possible
1004                 return self.buffer.write(str(x))
1005             return io.TextIOWrapper.write(self, x)
1006 
1007     else:
1008 
1009         def write(self, x):
1010             # try to use backslash and surrogate escape strategies before failing
1011             self._errors = (
1012                 "backslashescape" if self.encoding != "mbcs" else "surrogateescape"
1013             )
1014             try:
1015                 return io.TextIOWrapper.write(self, to_text(x, errors=self._errors))
1016             except UnicodeDecodeError:
1017                 if self._errors != "surrogateescape":
1018                     self._errors = "surrogateescape"
1019                 else:
1020                     self._errors = "replace"
1021                 return io.TextIOWrapper.write(self, to_text(x, errors=self._errors))
1022 
1023         def writelines(self, lines):
1024             for line in lines:
1025                 self.write(line)
1026 
1027     def __del__(self):
1028         try:
1029             self.detach()
1030         except Exception:
1031             pass
1032 
1033     def isatty(self):
1034         return self._stream.isatty()

1037 # More things borrowed from click, this is because we are using `TextIOWrapper` instead of
1038 # just a normal StringIO
1039 class _StreamProvider(object):
1040     def __init__(self, stream):
1041         self._stream = stream
1042         super(_StreamProvider, self).__init__()
1043 
1044     def __getattr__(self, name):
1045         return getattr(self._stream, name)
1046 
1047     def read1(self, size):
1048         fn = getattr(self._stream, "read1", None)
1049         if fn is not None:
1050             return fn(size)
1051         if six.PY2:
1052             return self._stream.readline(size)
1053         return self._stream.read(size)
1054 
1055     def readable(self):
1056         fn = getattr(self._stream, "readable", None)
1057         if fn is not None:
1058             return fn()
1059         try:
1060             self._stream.read(0)
1061         except Exception:
1062             return False
1063         return True
1064 
1065     def writable(self):
1066         fn = getattr(self._stream, "writable", None)
1067         if fn is not None:
1068             return fn()
1069         try:
1070             self._stream.write(b"")
1071         except Exception:
1072             return False
1073         return True
1074 
1075     def seekable(self):
1076         fn = getattr(self._stream, "seekable", None)
1077         if fn is not None:
1078             return fn()
1079         try:
1080             self._stream.seek(self._stream.tell())
1081         except Exception:
1082             return False
1083         return True

1092 def _isatty(stream):
1093     try:
1094         is_a_tty = stream.isatty()
1095     except Exception:  # pragma: no cover
1096         is_a_tty = False
1097     return is_a_tty

1100 _wrap_for_color = None
1101 
1102 try:
1103     import colorama
1104 except ImportError:
1105     colorama = None
1106 
1107 _color_stream_cache = WeakKeyDictionary()
1108 
1109 if os.name == "nt" or sys.platform.startswith("win"):
1110 
1111     if colorama is not None:
1112 
1113         def _is_wrapped_for_color(stream):
1114             return isinstance(
1115                 stream, (colorama.AnsiToWin32, colorama.ansitowin32.StreamWrapper)
1116             )
1117 
1118         def _wrap_for_color(stream, color=None):
1119             try:
1120                 cached = _color_stream_cache.get(stream)
1121             except KeyError:
1122                 cached = None
1123             if cached is not None:
1124                 return cached
1125             strip = not _can_use_color(stream, color)
1126             _color_wrapper = colorama.AnsiToWin32(stream, strip=strip)
1127             result = _color_wrapper.stream
1128             _write = result.write
1129 
1130             def _write_with_color(s):
1131                 try:
1132                     return _write(s)
1133                 except Exception:
1134                     _color_wrapper.reset_all()
1135                     raise
1136 
1137             result.write = _write_with_color
1138             try:
1139                 _color_stream_cache[stream] = result
1140             except Exception:
1141                 pass
1142             return result

1145 def _cached_stream_lookup(stream_lookup_func, stream_resolution_func):
1146     stream_cache = WeakKeyDictionary()
1147 
1148     def lookup():
1149         stream = stream_lookup_func()
1150         result = None
1151         if stream in stream_cache:
1152             result = stream_cache.get(stream, None)
1153         if result is not None:
1154             return result
1155         result = stream_resolution_func()
1156         try:
1157             stream = stream_lookup_func()
1158             stream_cache[stream] = result
1159         except Exception:
1160             pass
1161         return result
1162 
1163     return lookup

1166 def get_text_stream(stream="stdout", encoding=None):
1167     """Retrieve a utf-8 stream wrapper around **sys.stdout** or **sys.stderr**.
1168 
1169     :param str stream: The name of the stream to wrap from the :mod:`sys` module.
1170     :param str encoding: An optional encoding to use.
1171     :return: A new :class:`~vistir.misc.StreamWrapper` instance around the stream
1172     :rtype: `vistir.misc.StreamWrapper`
1173     """
1174 
1175     stream_map = {"stdin": sys.stdin, "stdout": sys.stdout, "stderr": sys.stderr}
1176     if os.name == "nt" or sys.platform.startswith("win"):
1177         from ._winconsole import _get_windows_console_stream, _wrap_std_stream
1178 
1179     else:
1180         _get_windows_console_stream = lambda *args: None  # noqa
1181         _wrap_std_stream = lambda *args: None  # noqa
1182 
1183     if six.PY2 and stream != "stdin":
1184         _wrap_std_stream(stream)
1185     sys_stream = stream_map[stream]
1186     windows_console = _get_windows_console_stream(sys_stream, encoding, None)
1187     if windows_console is not None:
1188         if _can_use_color(windows_console):
1189             return _wrap_for_color(windows_console)
1190         return windows_console
1191     return get_wrapped_stream(sys_stream, encoding)

1244 def echo(text, fg=None, bg=None, style=None, file=None, err=False, color=None):
1245     """Write the given text to the provided stream or **sys.stdout** by
1246     default.
1247 
1248     Provides optional foreground and background colors from the ansi defaults:
1249     **grey**, **red**, **green**, **yellow**, **blue**, **magenta**, **cyan**
1250     or **white**.
1251 
1252     Available styles include **bold**, **dark**, **underline**, **blink**, **reverse**,
1253     **concealed**
1254 
1255     :param str text: Text to write
1256     :param str fg: Foreground color to use (default: None)
1257     :param str bg: Foreground color to use (default: None)
1258     :param str style: Style to use (default: None)
1259     :param stream file: File to write to (default: None)
1260     :param bool color: Whether to force color (i.e. ANSI codes are in the text)
1261     """
1262 
1263     if file and not hasattr(file, "write"):
1264         raise TypeError("Expected a writable stream, received {!r}".format(file))
1265     if not file:
1266         if err:
1267             file = _text_stderr()
1268         else:
1269             file = _text_stdout()
1270     if text and not isinstance(text, (six.string_types, bytes, bytearray)):
1271         text = six.text_type(text)
1272     text = "" if not text else text
1273     if isinstance(text, six.text_type):
1274         text += "\n"
1275     else:
1276         text += b"\n"
1277     if text and six.PY3 and is_bytes(text):
1278         buffer = _get_binary_buffer(file)
1279         if buffer is not None:
1280             file.flush()
1281             buffer.write(text)
1282             buffer.flush()
1283             return
1284     if text and not is_bytes(text):
1285         can_use_color = _can_use_color(file, color=color)
1286         if any([fg, bg, style]):
1287             text = colorize(text, fg=fg, bg=bg, attrs=style)
1288         if not can_use_color or (os.name == "nt" and not _wrap_for_color):
1289             text = ANSI_REMOVAL_RE.sub("", text)
1290         elif os.name == "nt" and _wrap_for_color and not _is_wrapped_for_color(file):
1291             file = _wrap_for_color(file, color=color)
1292     if text:
